Independent F5 wire peer for sing-openconnect M3.

The authentication, profile, options, /myvpn, logout, F5 framing, and RFC1662
shim are independently implemented from the observable wire contracts in
OpenConnect commit 2035601b64a5360a46d18e08937e7f654b3230f2. The data plane is
terminated by Debian pppd 2.5.2-1+1. On Darwin hosts without a usable Docker
/dev/ppp, the harness runs the same peer against the system pppd 2.4.2 and
Homebrew OpenSSL 3.6.3. TLS uses Python's OpenSSL-backed ssl module; DTLS
1.0/1.2 uses the separately packaged OpenSSL s_server rather than the
production Go DTLS implementation.
